The <strong><code>HTMLSlotElement</code></strong> interface of the <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/Web_Components/Shadow_DOM">Shadow DOM API</a> enables access to the name and assigned nodes of an HTML <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/slot" title="The HTML &lt;slot&gt; element—part of the Web Components technology suite—is a placeholder inside a web component that you can fill with your own markup, which lets you create separate DOM trees and present them together."><code>&lt;slot&gt;</code></a> element.